Subject: [PATCH] drm: Don't test for IRQ support in VBLANK ioctls
Git-commit: 1e4cd78ed4932b08bc839392fa6784e03d8f9619
Patch-mainline: v5.15-rc1
References: bsc#1195464

For KMS drivers, replace the IRQ check in VBLANK ioctls with a check for
vblank support. IRQs might be enabled wthout vblanking being supported.

This change also removes the DRM framework's only dependency on IRQ state
for non-legacy drivers. For legacy drivers with userspace modesetting,
the original test remains in drm_wait_vblank_ioctl().

V4: * avoid preprocessor ifdef in drm_wait_vblank_ioctl()	  (Jani, Thierry)
V3: * optimize test in drm_wait_vblank_ioctl() for KMS case (Liviu)	* update docs for drm_irq_uninstall()
V2: * keep the old test for legacy drivers in	  drm_wait_vblank_ioctl() (Daniel)

